## Essential Community Plugins

### 1. Dataview (Required)
**Purpose**: Dynamic queries and data aggregation

**Settings**:
| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Enable JavaScript Queries | ON | Required for DataviewJS dashboards |
| Enable Inline Queries | ON | Allows `= this.updated` in text |
| Automatic View Refreshing | ON | Keeps queries current |
| Refresh Interval | 2500ms | Balance between freshness and performance |

**Query Types**:
- `LIST` — Simple bullet list
- `TABLE` — Structured data with columns
- `TASK` — Task aggregation
- `CALENDAR` — Date-based visualization

### 2. Templater (Required)
**Purpose**: Advanced templates with JavaScript

**Settings**:
| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Template Folder Location | `Templates/` | Central template storage |
| Trigger on New File Creation | ON | Auto-apply templates |
| Enable Folder Templates | ON | Different templates per folder |

**Folder Templates**:
| Folder | Template |
|--------|----------|
| `Journal/` | `Templates/Dev Session Log.md` |
| `Projects/` | `Templates/Project Template.md` |
| `Decisions/` | `Templates/ADR - Decision Record.md` |

**Useful Templater Syntax**:
```markdown
<%* /* JavaScript code */ _%>
<% tp.date.now("YYYY-MM-DD") %>
<% tp.file.title %>
<% tp.file.cursor() %>
```

### 3. Tasks (Required)
**Purpose**: Task management with due dates and priorities

**Settings**:
| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Global Task Filter | (empty) | All checkboxes are tasks |
| Auto-suggest | ON | Task syntax completion |
| Set done date | ON | Track completion |

**Task Syntax**:
```markdown
- [ ] Basic task
- [ ] Task with due date 📅 2025-12-20
- [ ] High priority task ⏫
- [ ] Task with scheduled date ⏳ 2025-12-15
- [x] Completed task ✅ 2025-12-14
```

**Priority Emojis**:
- ⏫ High
- 🔼 Medium
- 🔽 Low

### 4. Calendar (Required)
**Purpose**: Visual daily note navigation

**Settings**:
| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Week Start | Monday | Standard work week |
| Show Week Number | ON | Integrates with Periodic Notes |
| Words per dot | 250 | Visual indication of note size |

**Usage**: Click any date to create/open that day's note.

### 5. Periodic Notes (Recommended)
**Purpose**: Weekly, monthly, quarterly, yearly notes

**Settings**:
| Period | Folder | Format | Template |
|--------|--------|--------|----------|
| Weekly | `Journal/Weekly/` | `gggg-[W]ww` | `Templates/Weekly Review.md` |
| Monthly | `Journal/Monthly/` | `YYYY-MM` | `Templates/Monthly Review.md` |
| Quarterly | `Journal/Quarterly/` | `YYYY-[Q]Q` | `Templates/Quarterly Review.md` |
| Yearly | `Journal/Yearly/` | `YYYY` | `Templates/Yearly Review.md` |

